All Classes and Interfaces

Class
Description
Bishop
The Bishop represents a bishop on the chess board
Board
The Board class represents a 15x15 chess board on which GamePieces reside and the castles on either side
BoardPost
The BoardPost class represents a Post of a Board
Card
The Card represents a container which holds an Image of a GamePiece, along with energy, health, and damage information.
ChangePost
The ChangePost class represents a piece to be added to the board.
DrawingSurface
Represents a PApplet that holds all assets for this program.
GamePiece
the GamePiece represents a piece on a chess board
ImageCodes
Has the image codes for the image names.
IntegerPost
The IntegerPost class represents an integer.
Knight
The Knight represents a knight on the chess board
Location
The Location class represents a spot on the Board.
Main
The Main class is the class that contains the PApplet on which the program is executed.
Pawn
the Pawn represents a pawn on the chess board
Player
Represents a player in the game.
Post
The class you store in the database must fit 3 simple constraints: The class must have a default constructor that takes no arguments.
Queen
the Queen represents a queen on the chess board
Rook
the Rook represents a rook on the chess board
Screen
Abstract class representing a screen.
ScreenCodes
Has the screen codes for the Screens.
ScreenInstructions
This Screen displays basic instructions and controls for playing the game.
ScreenLocalGame
The screen that holds the game and its elements for the user to interact during a match (placing pieces, seeing enemy pieces, etc)
ScreenLocalNameCreate
This Screen is used for the user to enter names before they play a local game
ScreenMenu
Screen representing the menu that players first see when they join the game.
ScreenOnlineGame
This Screen holds the game and its elements for the user to interact with during a match (placing pieces, seeing enemy pieces, etc)
ScreenOnlineNameCreate
This Screen is used for the user to enter their name before they queue up for an online game.
ScreenQueue
This Screen is used as a waiting screen while the user is waiting for another player to play the game.
UserPost
The UserPost class represents a Post of a Player
